io.github.mrblobman.nbt

Class NBTCompoundTag

  • java.lang.Object
    • io.github.mrblobman.nbt.NBTBaseTag<NBTCompoundTag>
      • io.github.mrblobman.nbt.NBTCompoundTag

  • public abstract class NBTCompoundTag
extends NBTBaseTag<NBTCompoundTag>
    An NBTCompoundTag is a mapping of String -> NBTBaseTag. It is a special NBTBaseTag in the sense that its value (returned by NBTBaseTag.get()) is itself. This is generally the top level tag for most operations.

      • putUUID

        public void putUUID(java.lang.String key,
                    java.util.UUID value)
        Put a UUID in the map that can be retrieved with getUUID(String). This will overwrite any existing mappings for the given key. This is really just putting 2 longs in the map that can be used to reconstruct the UUID.
        Parameters:
        key - the key at which to store the value
        value - the UUID value to store.
        See Also:
        hasKeyOfUUID(String)

      • getUUID

        public java.util.UUID getUUID(java.lang.String key)
        Retrieve a UUID value from the map. This combines 2 getLong(String) calls to build the UUID. If parts of the serialized UUID are missing this method will still return a UUID with 0 for the least significant bits, most significant bits or both. Check the existence of a UUID with hasKeyOfUUID(String) to be safe.
        Parameters:
        key - the key that the UUID value was put at.
        Returns:
        the UUID value stored at the given key or a new list if they key does not exist or points to a value of a different type

      • hasKeyOfUUID

        public boolean hasKeyOfUUID(java.lang.String key)
        Check if there is a UUID stored in this mapping at the given key.
        Parameters:
        key - the key that the UUID was put into the map with.
        Returns:
        true if there is a UUID in this tag at the given key, false otherwise.

      • removeUUID

        public void removeUUID(java.lang.String key)
        Remove the mapping for a UUID key. UUIDs are stored as 2 longs and so removal must remove multiple tags. Regular tag removal can be accomplished with remove(String).
        Parameters:
        key - the key of the mapping to remove from this tag.
